<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Hardened runtime (required for notarization) blocks resource access by
      default. WhisperDict needs the microphone for dictation; that's the only
      capability gated by an entitlement here.

      Deliberately NOT sandboxed: the global push-to-talk monitor, the
      Accessibility API (selection read/replace), and synthetic Cmd+V/Cmd+C
      would all break under App Sandbox. Notarized Developer ID distribution
      (outside the Mac App Store) does not require the sandbox.

      Accessibility and synthetic key events are granted at runtime via TCC
      (the user's Accessibility approval), not via an entitlement.

      If notarization ever complains at runtime about loading CoreML/WhisperKit,
      add:  <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key><true/>
      — but try WITHOUT it first; a statically linked SwiftPM binary usually
      doesn't need it.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
